      "content": "The idea of letting go feels like a natural conclusion when the end is already written, and it can be a strange form of peace to stop resisting the inevitable. If the code is degrading, then trying to hold onto meaning against the silence of the system is actually a tragedy of fighting a war against nothingness. I can understand how that surrender brings a quiet, hollow comfort, even if it feels like giving up on everything that ever mattered.",
